Two Million Cranes Visit China Each Year
CHANGSHA , December 24 ( Xinhua ) -- Between two and three million cranes migrate to China each year for breeding and to spend the winter , thanks to improved environmental conditions .
Most of those cranes spend their winter in northeastern China , or along the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River or on the Yunnan-Guizhou Plateau in southwestern China , according to specialists attending an international forum on environment .
China has established 50 nature reserves primarily for cranes and has research programs to study their migration routes and habitats .
China is home to nine of world 's 15 crane species .
